  "uuid": "f30bd87e4e0ec268f0f7d7bcec7f3019",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Engineer",
  "description": "<h3>Job Summary</h3><p>The M&E Engineer is responsible for the planning, design coordination, installation, testing, and maintenance of mechanical and electrical systems in building and infrastructure projects. This role ensures all M&E works comply with statutory requirements, project specifications, safety standards, and quality expectations while meeting cost and schedule objectives.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p>Design & Coordination</p><ul><li><p>Review and coordinate M&E designs, drawings, specifications, and shop drawings.</p></li><li><p>Ensure integration and coordination between mechanical, electrical, architectural, and structural works.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with consultants, contractors, suppliers, and authorities to resolve technical issues.</p></li></ul><p>Site Supervision & Project Execution</p><ul><li><p>Supervise M&E installation works on site to ensure compliance with approved drawings and specifications.</p></li><li><p>Monitor progress, workmanship quality, and adherence to project schedules.</p></li><li><p>Attend site meetings and provide technical input and solutions.</p></li></ul><p>Testing, Commissioning & Handover</p><ul><li><p>Plan and witness testing, commissioning, and balancing of M&E systems.</p></li><li><p>Ensure systems are fully operational and meet performance requirements before handover.</p></li><li><p>Prepare operation & maintenance (O&M) manuals, as-built drawings, and handover documentation.</p></li></ul><p>Compliance & Safety</p><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with local authorities’ requirements (e.g. BCA, SCDF, PUB, EMA, NEA, MOM).</p></li><li><p>Ensure all works comply with relevant codes, standards, and safety regulations.</p></li><li><p>Enforce safe work practices and participate in risk assessments and toolbox meetings.</p></li></ul><p>Cost & Contract Administration</p><ul><li><p>Review M&E quotations, variation orders, and progress claims.</p></li><li><p>Assist in cost control and value engineering where applicable.</p></li><li><p>Evaluate technical submissions and material approvals.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements & Qualifications</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Engineering, Electrical Engineering, or related discipline.</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>8 years</strong> of relevant M&E experience in building or infrastructure projects.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with local codes, standards, and authority submission processes.</p></li><li><p>Able to read and interpret technical drawings and specifications.</p></li><li><p>Good coordination, communication, and problem-solving skills.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in AutoCAD and MS Office; BIM knowledge is an advantage.</p></li></ul><h3>Preferred Skills (Added Advantage)</h3><ul><li><p>Experience in commercial, institutional, industrial, or public sector projects.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of green building standards (e.g. Green Mark).</p></li><li><p>Hands-on site experience with testing and commissioning.</p></li></ul>",
